<p>[69] Author interviews, Nahm front, 2018. Names of interviewees, and dates and places of interviews withheld at intervieweesâ request.</p>
<p>[70] For a good overview of Lebanese border fighting between Hezbollah and Israel, see Nick Blanford, <i>Warriors of God: The Inside Story of Hezbollahâs Relentless War Against Israel</i> (New York: Random House, 2011).</p>
<p>[71] See <a onclick="javascript:pageTracker._trackPageview('/outgoing/www.washingtoninstitute.org/policy-analysis/view/border-fight-could-shift-saudi-arabias-yemen-war-calculus');"  href="https://www.washingtoninstitute.org/policy-analysis/view/border-fight-could-shift-saudi-arabias-yemen-war-calculus" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Lori Plotkin Boghardt and Michael Knights, âBorder Fight Could Shift Saudi Arabiaâs Yemen War Calculus,â Washington Institute for Near East Policy, December 6, 2016.</a></p>
